<subSubSection id="C30FB2903528FFE2FF47F867FBBDFF05" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="369" pageId="11" pageNumber="367" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BAAE11B3528FFE3FF47F867FBD3FE51" blockId="11.[151,1437,1941,2040]" lastBlockId="12.[151,1437,151,429]" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="368" pageId="11" pageNumber="367">
<emphasis id="B9613D093528FFE4FF47F867FD8BF853" bold="true" box="[199,548,1941,1968]" pageId="11" pageNumber="367">
Description. Male (
<typeStatus id="54AE5FB93528FFE4FE2BF867FDB8F853" box="[427,535,1941,1967]" pageId="11" pageNumber="367">holotype</typeStatus>
).
</emphasis>
Total length: 4.56. Carapace dark brown, 2.18 long, 1.63 wide, 1.31 high (
<figureCitation id="132EFD9E3528FFE4FAEAF867FF4DF828" captionStart="FIGURES 40–43" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1835,1859]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,358,1802]" captionTargetId="figure-99@11.[151,1435,345,1812]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 40–43. T. colombiaenpaz sp. nov., male holotype (ICN-Ar 8263), 40 habitus; 41 cephalothorax, lateral view; female paratype (ICN-Ar 8264); 42 habitus; 43 cephalotorax, lateral view. Scale bars = 1.00 mm (40, 42), 0.50 mm (41, 43)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501146" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501146/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="367">Figs 40–41</figureCitation>
). OC dark brown, 0.98 long. Anterior eye row 1.55 wide and posterior 1.42 wide. As in the remaining species in the genus, the PME are unusually enlarged compared to the others. Sternum greenish-black, 1.00 long, 0.79 wide. Labium yellowish-brown, 0.23 long, 0.30 wide. Chelicerae dark brown, with two retromarginal and three promarginal teeth. Palp dark brown, with a curved embolus, small median apophysis (ma), tibia with a larger proventral apophysis (PvTa), and the retrolateral apophysis together with the retroventral apophysis (RvTa) form an extended concavity (
<figureCitation id="132EFD9E352FFFE3FE00FEF1FDACFEE1" box="[384,515,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 44–50" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1549,1573]" captionTargetBox="[159,1423,466,1522]" captionTargetId="figure-181@12.[151,1435,453,1526]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 44–50. T. colombiaenpaz sp. nov., male holotype (ICN-Ar 8263), 44 male palp, prolateral view; 45–46 same, ventral view; 47–48 same, retrolateral view; female paratype (ICN-Ar 8264), 49 epigynum, ventral view; 50 same, cleared, dorsal view. Abbreviations: cd=copulatory duct, co=copulatory opening, e=embolus, ma=median apophysis, PvTa=proventral tibial apophysis, RTA=retrolateral tibial apophysis, RvTa=retroventral tibial apophysis, sd=sperm duct, sp=spermatheca. Scale bars = 0.20 mm (44–48), 0.10 mm (49–50)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501148" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501148/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="368">Figs 44–48</figureCitation>
). Leg formula: 4321, all yellow with black marks. Leg macrosetae: I, III p 1 di; II p 1 di, d 1 di; patella, I–III p 1 me; IV p 1 me, r 1 me; tibia, I v 2–2–2, p 1 me; II v 1–2–2, p 1–0–1; III v 1–1–1, p 1–0–1, r 1–0–1, d 1 pr; IV v 1–2–2, p 1–0–1, r 1–0–1, d 1 pr; metatarsus, I v 2–1–2; II v 2–1–1, p 1–0–1; III v 2–0–2, p 1–0–1, r 1–0–1; IV v 2–0–2, p 1–1–0–1, r 1–1–0–1. Abdomen greenish-brown with a disperse pattern of yellow points, four dimpled spots in the medial area and posteromedial chevron marks (
<figureCitation id="132EFD9E352FFFE3FB9BFE61FBDFFE51" box="[1051,1136,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–43" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1835,1859]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,358,1802]" captionTargetId="figure-99@11.[151,1435,345,1812]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 40–43. T. colombiaenpaz sp. nov., male holotype (ICN-Ar 8263), 40 habitus; 41 cephalothorax, lateral view; female paratype (ICN-Ar 8264); 42 habitus; 43 cephalotorax, lateral view. Scale bars = 1.00 mm (40, 42), 0.50 mm (41, 43)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501146" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501146/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="368">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF6AB193352FFFE3FF17F9FFFD8EF94A" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501148" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6501148" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501148/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="368" startId="12.[151,264,1549,1573]" targetBox="[159,1423,466,1522]" targetPageId="12">
<paragraph id="8BAAE11B352FFFE3FF17F9FFFD8EF94A" blockId="12.[151,1436,1549,1718]" pageId="12" pageNumber="368">
<emphasis id="B9613D09352FFFE3FF17F9FFFEFCF9DA" bold="true" box="[151,339,1549,1574]" pageId="12" pageNumber="368">FIGURES 44–50.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C159A98352FFFE3FED8F9FCFDA6F9DA" authority="Muñoz-Charry &amp; Galvis &amp; Martínez, 2022" authorityName="Muñoz-Charry &amp; Galvis &amp; Martínez" authorityYear="2022" box="[344,521,1550,1574]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Thrandina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="12" pageNumber="368" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colombiaenpaz" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9613D09352FFFE3FED8F9FCFDA6F9DA" box="[344,521,1550,1574]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="368">T. colombiaenpaz</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9613D09352FFFE3FD8EF9FCFDF1F9DA" bold="true" box="[526,606,1550,1574]" pageId="12" pageNumber="368">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2528072352FFFE3FD8EF9FCFDF1F9DA" box="[526,606,1550,1574]" pageId="12" pageNumber="368" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, male holotype (ICN-Ar 8263), 44 male palp, prolateral view; 45–46 same, ventral view; 47–48 same, retrolateral view; female paratype (ICN-Ar 8264), 49 epigynum, ventral view; 50 same, cleared, dorsal view. Abbreviations: cd=copulatory duct, co=copulatory opening, e=embolus, ma=median apophysis, PvTa=proventral tibial apophysis, RTA=retrolateral tibial apophysis, RvTa=retroventral tibial apophysis, sd=sperm duct, sp=spermatheca. Scale bars = 0.20 mm (44–48), 0.10 mm (49–50).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BAAE11B352FFFE2FF47F916FB9AFF29" blockId="12.[151,1437,1763,2043]" lastBlockId="13.[151,1437,151,357]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="369" pageId="12" pageNumber="368">
<emphasis id="B9613D09352FFFE3FF47F916FDF0F901" bold="true" box="[199,607,1763,1790]" pageId="12" pageNumber="368">
Female. (
<typeStatus id="54AE5FB9352FFFE3FEB5F911FE0BF901" box="[309,420,1763,1789]" pageId="12" pageNumber="368">paratype</typeStatus>
, ICN-Ar 8277).
</emphasis>
Total length 4.95. Carapace dark brown, 2.09 long, 1.64 wide, 1.27 high (
<figureCitation id="132EFD9E352FFFE3FF1FF8FAFE8BF8DE" box="[159,292,1800,1826]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–43" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1835,1859]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,358,1802]" captionTargetId="figure-99@11.[151,1435,345,1812]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 40–43. T. colombiaenpaz sp. nov., male holotype (ICN-Ar 8263), 40 habitus; 41 cephalothorax, lateral view; female paratype (ICN-Ar 8264); 42 habitus; 43 cephalotorax, lateral view. Scale bars = 1.00 mm (40, 42), 0.50 mm (41, 43)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501146" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501146/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="368">Figs 42–43</figureCitation>
). OC dark brown, 1.01 long. Anterior eye row 1.55 wide and posterior 1.43 wide. Sternum greenishblack, 0.97 long, 0.71 wide. Labium yellowish-brown, 0.31 long, 0.36 wide. Chelicerae dark brown, with two retromarginal and three promarginal teeth. Leg formula: 4321, all brown with dark brown spots. Leg macrosetae: femur, I, III p 1 di; II p 1 di, d 1 di; patella, I–II p 1 me; III–IV p 1 me, r 1 me; tibia, I v 2–2–2, p 1 me; II v 1–1–2, p 1–0–1; III v 1–1–1, p 1–0–1, r 1–0–1; IV v 1–2–1, p 1–0–1, r 1–0–1, d 1 pr; metatarsus, I v 2–1–2; II v 2–0–2, p 1–0–1; III v 1–0–1, p 1–0–2, r 1–0–1, d 1 pr; IV v 2–0–1, p 1–1–0–2, r 1–1–0–2. Abdomen greenish-brown with a dispersed pattern of yellow points and four dimpled spots in the medial area (
<figureCitation id="132EFD9E352FFFE3FBA3F812FBD6F806" box="[1059,1145,2016,2042]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–43" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1835,1859]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,358,1802]" captionTargetId="figure-99@11.[151,1435,345,1812]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 40–43. T. colombiaenpaz sp. nov., male holotype (ICN-Ar 8263), 40 habitus; 41 cephalothorax, lateral view; female paratype (ICN-Ar 8264); 42 habitus; 43 cephalotorax, lateral view. Scale bars = 1.00 mm (40, 42), 0.50 mm (41, 43)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501146" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501146/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="368">Fig. 42</figureCitation>
). Epigynum (
<figureCitation id="132EFD9E352FFFE3FA93F812FA3BF807" box="[1299,1428,2016,2043]" captionStart="FIGURES 44–50" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1549,1573]" captionTargetBox="[159,1423,466,1522]" captionTargetId="figure-181@12.[151,1435,453,1526]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 44–50. T. colombiaenpaz sp. nov., male holotype (ICN-Ar 8263), 44 male palp, prolateral view; 45–46 same, ventral view; 47–48 same, retrolateral view; female paratype (ICN-Ar 8264), 49 epigynum, ventral view; 50 same, cleared, dorsal view. Abbreviations: cd=copulatory duct, co=copulatory opening, e=embolus, ma=median apophysis, PvTa=proventral tibial apophysis, RTA=retrolateral tibial apophysis, RvTa=retroventral tibial apophysis, sd=sperm duct, sp=spermatheca. Scale bars = 0.20 mm (44–48), 0.10 mm (49–50)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501148" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501148/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="368">Figs 49–50</figureCitation>
) with a big and posteriorly oval copulatory opening (co), short-wide copulatory ducts, with a ventral and posterior insertion of the copulatory ducts (cd) in the bigger and rounded spermathecae (sp).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAAE11B352EFFE2FF47FF2CFBBDFF05" blockId="13.[151,1437,151,357]" box="[199,1042,222,250]" pageId="13" pageNumber="369">
<emphasis id="B9613D09352EFFE2FF47FF2CFE90FF04" bold="true" box="[199,319,222,248]" pageId="13" pageNumber="369">Variation.</emphasis>
(n= 
<specimenCount id="9D132A92352EFFE2FEEDFF2DFE6AFF06" box="[365,453,223,250]" pageId="13" pageNumber="369" type="male">2 males</specimenCount>
) Total length 4.56–5.09. Carapace length 2.18–2.57.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30FB290352EFFE2FF47FEF0FDD0FE99" pageId="13" pageNumber="369" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BAAE11B352EFFE2FF47FEF0FDD0FE99" blockId="13.[151,1437,151,357]" pageId="13" pageNumber="369">
<emphasis id="B9613D09352EFFE2FF47FEF0FD8EFEE0" bold="true" box="[199,545,258,285]" pageId="13" pageNumber="369">Distribution and Comments.</emphasis>
Known only from its 
<typeStatus id="54AE5FB9352EFFE2FCA4FEF1FCFBFEE1" box="[804,852,259,285]" pageId="13" pageNumber="369">type</typeStatus>
locality in the Colombian Andes (
<figureCitation id="132EFD9E352EFFE2FB62FEF1FA96FEE1" box="[1250,1337,258,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 57" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1890,1914]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-22@15.[164,1423,181,1866]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 57. Distribution of jumping spiders of the tribe Lapsiini Maddison (Salticidae: Spartaeinae) in South America. The figures with a dot inside represent the type species of each genus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501154" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501154/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="369">Fig. 57</figureCitation>
). All the material examined was collected in a well-conserved Andean moist forest, by beating in the day moss-covered trunks and the mosses placed in rock-walls.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
